CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 4, 1962, pg. 9 reads:"Mr. And Mrs. Howard U. Prentiss...Harris photo" Portion of accompanying article reads: "Miss Toni Howell, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Jack Howell was a beautiful bride as she pledged her troth to Howard U. Prentiss, of Washington, D.C.  The happy pair repeated vows before Rev. James C. Cayce of Ebenezer Baptist Church.  The ceremony was enchanting, held in prettily decorated garden of the bride's home..."
TitMainTitle: Man, possibly Jack Howell, standing beside bride Toni Howell walking down stairs of porch at home of Mr. and Mrs. Jack Howell
